.TH PERSIST-SAVE 1 "June 2026" "mx-remaster" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
persist-save \- save live-system changes into the persistence filesystem
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B persist-save
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B persist-save
copies changes from the running live system into the persistence filesystem.
It is the manual save command for live systems that use root persistence.
The tool checks that dynamic persistence is enabled, ensures the persistence
volume is available, and then synchronizes the live changes back into the
persisted root filesystem.

This command is generally used at shutdown or when the user wants to save
changes immediately.
It can also store volume settings when ALSA is available.
.SH OPTIONS
.B persist-save
does not define any tool-specific options.
It does honor the shared antiX common options such as quiet and GUI/CLI mode
selection.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /live/config/initrd.out
Live configuration used to verify that dynamic persistence is enabled.
.TP
.I /live/config/last-persist-save
Timestamp written after a successful save.
.TP
.I /live/config/save-persist
Legacy trigger file used by the surrounding live workflow.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR persist-config (1),
.BR persist-makefs (1),
.BR rsync (1)
.SH AUTHOR
mx-remaster maintainers
